*******************
*  INTRODUCTION   *
*******************
Pacman 3D is a simple demostrate game built with OpenGL.


**********
*  GOAL  *
**********
The goal is to control your pacman(the yellow ball on the screen center) to
eat all the beans in the map.
BUT you don't let your pacman to be eaten by other monsters walking in the
map, or you will fail.


*************
*  CONTROL  *
*************
On Splash Window:
ENTER -- Start a new game

In the game:
W -- Move Up
S -- Move Down
A -- Move Left
D -- Move Right


*************
*  COMPILE  *
*************
1. Windows
Install MinGW and Glut for MinGW and Open a Console Window such as Windows's
built-in 'Command Prompt', MSYS or anything like this. Locate to the source 
code directory and enter the following command:
C:\Pacman3D>make

3. GNU/Linux
Install GNU Build Toolchain and Glut development package, open a terminal, 
locate to the source code directory then enter the following command
$ make


****************
*  COMPATIBLE  *
****************
This game uses standard OpenGL interface and works on both UNIX like Operating 
Systems and Windows, it has been tested on the following platforms:
 * GNU/Linux
 * Windows XP


